<br>
Then the backlash. <br>
<br>
The backlash for me personally was the fact that the damm movie got so huge. It seemed like every other commercial, televison show, or movie included a Matrix fight scene style parody.  This really took the magic out of it all for me, and when the next installment came out I did not go see it right away.<br>
<br>
Next thing I know everyone on the internet is either treating Reloaded like the second coming of christ or the worst thing to happen to cinema since Pauly Shore. When the hell did it go from a fun action-sci fi feature to the bane of ape headed jocks and the holy grail of tech geeks? After reading numerous messageboard posts and website reviews expounding on the parallels between the Relaoded script and the entire history of world civilization and religious development, while on the other end of the spectrum hearing it was mostly a snooze fest withnot enough action and special effects, I decided not to go see it at all.  I still havent rented the DVD.<br>
<br>
Now so far it is more of the same. <br>
<br>
Dont get me wrong, the commentaries such as the one in this thread explaining the philosophical implications of the films are compelling to say the least, even without having seen the movies. In fact maybe after reading all that stuff I feel like the movie would pale in comparison, or that I dont really need to see it anyway since I have heard in depth analysis of every nuance.<br>
<br>
I really dont know what I am getting at here, maybe this is my two cents. It just strikes me that the first film was intended to be a visual and somewhat mental extravaganza, certainly catering to the techno geek contingent but obviously enjoyable for joe six pack at the same time. The sequels, from the sound of it, have divided the viewing audience and have gone into realms that perhaps the original premise was never designed to support.  I suppose I will end up seeing them someday, maybe watching all three DVDs in a row when Revolutions comes out, after some of the hype has died back down again.  Then I can make my own decision at a little more distance form the rampant opinions and spoilers currently on the internet. I worry that I am missing something by forgoing the theater experience, but honestly, if i can just avoid the internet long enough to see RotK in the first week of release I will be happy. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=554649">Fammaden Flycaster</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.hneguild.com" target="top">Heaven and Earth</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morloc>Morloc</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:orange;'>Tavern Resident</span></span><br>  Posts: 679<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(11/7/03 1:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3653.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~lnalewajk/_images/Scrimm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=le